    {
      "id": "32e2a13f_393e2c24",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/vfc/charts/vfc-catalog/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "This is not going to work.\n\nFrom your code:\n\nif [ $REG_TO_MSB ]; then\n    sed -i \"s|REG_TO_MSB_WHEN_START.*|REG_TO_MSB_WHEN_START = True|\" vfc/nfvo/catalog/catalog/pub/config/config.py\nfi\n\nSo whenever the REG_TO_MSB is set, no matter if it's set to true or false as long as it's not empty string your final variable in a python code will be True which is probably not what you expected.\n\nNow being honest. Your current design is terrible. Doing sed from docker entrypoint script to apply configuration from helm chart is extremely fragile and may give unexpected results. Instead of that you should commit your config.py file to OOM repo, modify using provided values and then provide it in a ready form to container as a ConfigMap. For sensitive stuff you may use init container approach as for example here:\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/oom/+/101856/",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
